From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Petr=20=C5=A0tetiar?= <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
Date: Tue, 17 Sep 2024 11:30:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PROVISORY: vendor: make DeviceInfo availability optional
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

obuspa should not connect to the broker until several critical USP
Services have registered, but we're currently still experiencing
quite a lot of cases, where Device.DeviceInfo. fails to register, which
currently makes CDRouter test fails as obuspa doesn't connect to the
controller in time.

Since we want to proceed with the testing in those cases anyway, lets make the
Device.DeviceInfo. service optional and thus allow connection even in
cases Device.DeviceInfo. service failed to register.

This is just a temporary measure, we're still going to catch those
issues in the CDRouter USP testing using prpl HL-API tests.

References: PCF-1198
Signed-off-by: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
---
 src/vendor/vendor.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/vendor/vendor.c b/src/vendor/vendor.c
index 1ffba87457ec..13b0da73655a 100644
--- a/src/vendor/vendor.c
+++ b/src/vendor/vendor.c
@@ -60,8 +60,7 @@ static bool can_mtp_connect(void)
    // Exit if tr181-device has not registered the critical objects it provides for the data model
    if (USP_DM_IsRegistered(DM_DEVICE_DEVICEINFO) == false)
    {
-       USP_LOG_Warning("%s: Not connecting to Controller ACS as DeviceInfo is not registerd yet", __FUNCTION__);
-       return false;
+       USP_LOG_Warning("%s: DeviceInfo is not registered yet", __FUNCTION__);
    }
 
    // Exit if tr181-device has not registered the Device.Time data model
